Neil St. Blues has some of the best food in town, hands down. Literally everything on their menu is on-point. Their catfish is unmatched in Champaign/Urbana. I recently ordered some food from them through DoorDash (the pick 3 meal with catfish, chicken, shrimp, and 2 sides, which were collard greens with turkey and red beans and rice, both to die for) and it took forever for a driver to become available (obviously not Neil St. Blues' fault). I almost cancelled, but then a driver picked up my food at the last minute. I was expecting lukewarm, if not cold food that i would have to microwave. But no, the food was all warm and fresh when it arrived, leading me to conclude that they re-cooked my order after it sat out too long. That kind of customer service is rare and amazing.

I am disabled.  I cannot wear a mask. I do however wear a full faceshield.  I had an order for pickup.  I live out of town. I got there,  my order was not ready. I was told the faceshield was not allowed.  I already paid for my food. They made me put on a mask. I could not breathe,  got dizzy,  things went black for a second.  I explained my health issues. Heck, I have a cane. Asked if they could bring my food to the door.  After 10 minutes standing outside in the rain while customers laughed at me,I left. When I ordered,  it did not state I could not pick up my food with a faceshield on. I paid already. If I had known this would be an issue, I would not have ordered from them. Wasted my time and money. I am also going to point out. I ordered online for pickup so I could have as little contact as possible with people.  The gentleman at the door making me walk all the way across the bar to get an order I already paid for does not do that. If he had just told me that my order was not ready, I could have come back.

DELICIOUS! We ordered off of GrubHub, got catfish, which came with mac and cheese and candied yams, a vegan oyster mushroom po boy sandwich, and extra fries. We live across town from Neil Street blues about 5 miles and our food was delivered hot. The cat fish was meaty and succulent, crispy on the outside with a mild seasoned breading. Unfortunately I can't say much about the Mac and Cheese because I did not savor it delicately, rather I wolfed it down, taking quite large bites and chewing lethargicly, swallowing mostly whole noodles and figuratively "throwing back" the cheese. I was too excited, next time I will order a bigger portion. The Oyster Mushroom Po'boy sandwich was filling, the texture and taste were satisfying, the veggies were fresh. I was happy to find so many vegetarian and even vegan options on their menu. Will try the vegan Jambalaya next time.  Fries are fries, but Neil St Blues' are better. Currently eating the candied yams as a desert, they are sweet and yummy. I plan to refrigerate some and eat them cold later after my numed edible kicks in.  I'll for sure be ordering from here again. Thank you NSB!

My overall recommendation is to avoid this place. The atmosphere is decent, but the food and service were mediocre at best.  I had ordered the chili and a yardbird sandwich. The chili was okay, but too salty, and the sandwich was quite a bit underseasoned. My friend ordered the Blues Burger cooked medium, but it came out more well done, which made it much tougher and harder to eat. Another friend also ordered a fried shrimp po boy which was so salty it was actually inedible. This may have been a one off experience but everything we ordered, with the exception of a salad, was either over or under seasoned.  The service was also mediocre. When we arrived, we were led to a table that had not been cleared yet, so we had to wait a few minutes for it to be cleared. This is not a huge issue, and is normally one I would overlook. After we sat down, the waitress took our drink orders and nearly everyone at the table got water. However, it took an extremely long time for the drinks to come despite being such simple orders, and given that there were not many other patrons in the restaurant. Then after we ordered, the food also took forever to come out. It was at least 20 minutes for even the soups to come. Then after we had started eating the entrees, our waitress did not even stop to check up on us. My friend who ordered the salty shrimp po boy was out of water for around 10 minutes before the waitress finally came and refilled our drinks.  Overall, our group of 6 spent $25 per person and over two hours of our time for mediocre-to-indelible food, underwhelming service, and a generic atmosphere. It left all of us with a bad taste in our mouths and we would not come back here.

We sat down I asked for the beer menu and my waiter (who was lovely) had no idea where the menu was or IF THEY EVEN HAD ONE! We ordered the nachos which were bad at best. The cheese tasted purely processed almost as if it came out of a can. The chicken on the nachos were rubbery and clearly had been frozen. My date ordered the triple threat burger which was also with out a doubt frozen and bland. I ordered the catfish which had the consistency of brand new Goodyear tires. Pure rubber. I had potato salad on the side, I couldn’t take more than the initial bite as it was the most vinager and mustard flavored slop I’ve ever eaten. The fries were good if you like ketchup. I wouldn’t recommend this establishment to anyone unless you participate in trivia night get hammered first then eat. If I was drunk this would be 5 stars.

This was an amazing experience. We we're greated and seated immediately.  They are only open for lunch on Friday through the week. The Friday special is a whole catfish and spaghetti and it's a lot of food. One of my friends had this and loves it.  I had the Philly cheese steak egg rolls. Let me tell you they we're sooooo delicious!  Another friend had the pulled pork sandwich and sweet potato waffle fries. She was equally impressed, especially with the fries.  We had good service and an overall great experience!

1st of many visits. Walking in, think upscale southern cooking. It is downtown after all. I agree with another reviewer that more could be done ambiance-wise that could lend itself to that concept. Playing blues all day doesnt carry that. I appreciate cleanliness, good service, and good food. Tables and place were clean, but utensils had soap residue. Menu is simple and easy to read. Service was good with a smile, but I may have ordered another drink had I had more attention. Food was perfect really. Catfish was hot and breaded well, okra was spot on, and the sweet potato fries had a splash of brown sugar which was a nice touch. Ribs fell off the bone and smoked well. BIG portions! After I asked for the drink menu (?!) I noticed a small, but well rounded selection. I tip according to the overall experience and left 20%. I have every intention of returning with friends. I hope this helps.

The food was really good! I got fried catfish, cole slaw, fries, and sweet potato pie. Everything was so good! The catfish had a nice, crisp cornmeal breading. Their cole slaw was very close to KFC's, which is my favorite style. The fries were medium-sized width, crunchy on the outside and tender on the inside. The sweet potato pie tasted freshly made, was slightly warm, had a nice flakey crust, and some whipped cream. Yum!  My husband got four big, full-sized, fried chicken wings, fries, and mac and cheese. He liked his dinner, too, except that the M&C wasn't cheesy enough, in his opinion.

My first visit here. I sat in the Dublin side.  Literally no changes at all.  Atmosphere is drab. They have way too much fried food.  I had the cajun pasta which was actually very good.  If I go back it will be to try the gumbo.  I would describe it as medium quality bar food with cajun seasoning. Priced accordingly.

To start off, almost all the food our group had here was excellent! We ordered the fried catfish and shrimp and grits. The catfish, okra, fries, cornbread, and shrimp and grits we're awesome! Their cheese curds are some of the best I've had in town. The collard greens were just okay. There was also live music blues singers that provided excellent entertainment during our meal. The only reason I rate it lower than a 5 was the slow service. All the staff was super friendly, but they definitely have some organizational issues to work out. Our food kept being brought out to the wrong table, we waited a super long time before ordering and for our food to arrive. They're still relatively new so I'm sure they will be more organized in the coming months. I would definitely recommend giving it a try if you haven't yet!
